Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
ecoSplitCombinationalCell(25.10)              ecoSplitCombinationalCell(25.10)

Name
       ecoSplitCombinationalCell - Splits all multi-bit combinational cell in-
       stances to single-bit combinational cells

Syntax
       ecoSplitCombinationalCell

       [-help]

       [-force]

       [-fullSplit]

       [-legal]

       [-skipRoute]

       -inst  <combInstName>  |  {{Mbcb1  combCell1}  {Mbcb2  combCell2}...} |
       -listFile <fileName> | -all

       -preCTS | -postCTS | -postRoute

       Splits all multi-bit combinational cell instances to single-bit  combi-
       national  cells.  You  can  specify  the names of the combinational in-
       stances to be merged or you can specify the file  containing  names  of
       multi-bit instances to be split.

       Naming Convention During Splitting

       When splitting Multibit combinational cells, it will split the names as
       follows:

              * hier1/hier2/i_[0:3]

                TO

                hier1/hier2/i_[0:3]__0,                hier1/hier2/i_[0:3]__1,
                hier1/hier2/i_[0:3]__2, hier1/hier2/i_[0:3]__3

              * CDN_MB_abc_MB_def

                TO

                abc, def

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each  ecoSplitCombinationalCell parameter. For a
              detailed description of the command and all of  its  parameters,
              use the man command:  man ecoSplitCombinationalCell.

       -all   Splits  all  multi-bit  combinational cell instances to SBFF in-
              stances.

              This parameter is mutually exclusive with the -inst  and  -list-
              File parameters. At least one of these parameters must be speci-
              fied.

              Default: false

       -force Forces the splitting of the combinational cell regardless of the
              timing gains.

              Default: false

       -fullSplit
              Set  this  parameter  to completely split the multi-bit combina-
              tional cells to single bits.

       -inst <comboInstName >{{<Mbcb1 combCell1>} {<Mbcb2 combCell2>}...}
              Specifies the names of the combinational instance to  be  split.
              If  the input is a string of multi-bit combinational (MBCB)/Cell
              pairs list, it will split the MBCB to the specified cell without
              evaluation

              This parameter is mutually exclusive with the -listFile and -all
              parameters. At least one of these parameters must be specified.

       -legal Specifies to place the split flip-combinational cells  at  legal
              location.

              Default: false

       -listFile <fileName>
              Specifies  the file containing names of MBCB instances to split.
              Specify one instance on one line. Comment with #. Instance  name
              should  not  contain  spaces or backslashes. And if one instance
              and one cell is specified on one line, it will split the MBCB to
              the specified cell without evaluation.

              This parameter is mutually exclusive with the -inst and -all pa-
              rameters. At least one of these parameters must be specified.

       -postCTS
              Specify this parameter if the design stage is postCTS. This is a
              required parameter. One of these parameters, -preCTS,  -postCTS,
              or -postRoute must be specified.

       -postRoute
              Specify this parameter if the design stage is postRoute. This is
              a   required   parameter.  One  of  these  parameters,  -preCTS,
              -postCTS, or  -postRoute must be specified.

       -preCTS
              Specify this parameter if the design stage is preCTS. This is  a
              required  parameter. One of these parameters, -preCTS, -postCTS,
              or -postRoute must be specified.

       -skipRoute
              Specify this parameter if the  design  stage  is  postRoute  and
              routing is not required after the split.

